<item>
            <title>[LU-16944] lfs find: incomplete results when multiple paths precede negated expression</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16944</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When lfs find is used with multiple paths, the final path is not searched if the first option following that path is a &lt;tt&gt;!&lt;/tt&gt; or an option without an argument, like &lt;tt&gt;print&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-bash&quot;&gt;
$ mkdir /mnt/lustre/{a,b}
$ touch /mnt/lustre/{a,b}/f

$ lfs find /mnt/lustre/{a,b} ! -type d
/mnt/lustre/a/f

$ lfs find /mnt/lustre/{a,b} -print
/mnt/lustre/a
/mnt/lustre/a/f &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
